meanings.english_definition: Relating to both the tympanic and squamous parts of the temporal bone.

examples.sentence: The tympanosquamosal suture is located in the temporal bone.
examples.translation: 鼓室鱗状縫合は側頭骨に位置する。

etymology.value: From tympano- (referring to the tympanic part of the temporal bone) + squamosal (referring to the squamous part of the temporal bone).
